{"main_content":"<div id=\"tabSelect\"> <h1>Module 2: Exchanging Information<\/h1> <a href=\"\/2\/1\" class=\"nextTab\" style=\"display: inline-block;\">Intro <\/a> <a href=\"\/2\/2\" class=\"nextTab\" style=\"display: inline-block;\">Videos<\/a> <a href=\"\/2\/3\" class=\"currentTab\" style=\"display: inline-block;\">Quiz<\/a> <\/div> <form id=\"assessmentPage\" method=\"POST\" action=\"results\" onselectstart=\"return false;\"> <h2>Quiz<\/h2> <p class=\"encounteringQuiz\">  <label for=\"encountering1\">1. In the video, Mike Brown demonstrated the following red flags for driving  safety:<\/label>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering1\" value=\"1\">A. He quickly answered all questions<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering1\" value=\"2\">B. He needed to use both hands to sign his name<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering1\" value=\"3\">C. His hands were shaking a great deal<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering1\" value=\"4\">D. Both B and C<\/span> <\/p> <p class=\"encounteringQuiz\">  <label for=\"encountering2\">2. If an applicant turns his\/her head at different angles to try and look  at documents or items in front of them, it may be an indication they have  a vision problem:<\/label>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering2\" value=\"1\">True<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering2\" value=\"2\">False<\/span> <\/p> <p class=\"encounteringQuiz\">  <label for=\"encountering3\">3. What \u201cred flags\u201d for driving safety did Betty demonstrate in  the video:<\/label>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering3\" value=\"1\">A. She does not appear confused, and easily answers questions<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering3\" value=\"2\">B. Her daughter insisted on staying with her during the interaction<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering3\" value=\"3\">C. She appears \u201ctoo old\u201d to drive<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering3\" value=\"4\">D. Both A and B<\/span> <\/p> <p class=\"encounteringQuiz\">  <label for=\"encountering4\">4. In the video, Betty\u2019s daughter answered all the questions and  helped the applicant understand why she was there. Why might  this be a red flag for driving safety?<\/label>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering4\" value=\"1\">A. The applicant understands simple directions<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering4\" value=\"2\">B. The applicant does not appear able to function without assistance<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering4\" value=\"3\">C. The applicant has no difficulty with simple tasks<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering4\" value=\"4\">D. All of the above<\/span> <\/p> <p class=\"encounteringQuiz\">  <label for=\"encountering5\">5. What are common \u201cred flags\u201d that an applicant may have thinking and  memory problems:<\/label>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering5\" value=\"1\">A. Being generally confused and needing to be told many times in order  to follow simple directions<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering5\" value=\"2\">B. Producing the incorrect document or card multiple times after being instructed to show their current driver license<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering5\" value=\"3\">C. The applicant appears to have difficulty understanding simple directions<\/span>  <span>  <input type=\"radio\" name=\"encountering5\" value=\"4\">D. All of the above<\/span> <\/p> <p>  <button type=\"submit\">Quiz results<\/button> <\/p> <\/form>","page_title":"Module 2: Quiz"}